There is created within the Cabinet for Economic Development the Department for Business Development, which shall be headed by a commissioner appointed by the Governor. The department shall work with each Kentucky county in:
Assisting community-based economic development agencies in creating and implementing their respective work plans;
Developing cooperative interaction with existing industries and small and minority businesses and assisting export development;
Providing sufficient technical resources to create and maintain a database to facilitate sales transactions between Kentucky businesses;
Assisting minority businesses with federal, state, and local government agencies, regulations, and procurement programs; and
Introducing entrepreneurs to individual investors and to investment capital firms interested in start-up and early-state financing.

The Department for Business Development shall include the following divisions, each of which shall be headed by an executive director appointed by the secretary pursuant to KRS 12.050:
The Office of Entrepreneurship shall be responsible for various forms of small business assistance, including without being limited to:
Providing comprehensive information on all state business licenses and requirements;
Assisting businesses in the identification of government procurement opportunities;
Administering the innovation assistance set forth in KRS 154.12-278; and
Collecting, summarizing, and disseminating information helpful to small businesses, including information on: (a) Market research;
Federal, state, and local minority business programs; and
The availability of managerial assistance.
Research activities related to strategic planning, business site selection,
Program analysis;
Competitive analysis;
Communications and marketing services; and
Event planning. The Commission on Small Business Advocacy established in KRS 11.200 shall advise the office on small business needs; and (b) The Office of Research and Public Affairs, which shall administer the following: and existing industry; The office shall include the Division of Database and Systems Development, which shall be headed by a director appointed by the secretary pursuant to KRS 12.050.
